加号 '''+''' 即拉丁语 {{lang|la|et}} 的简化，意为「与」，和符号 '''[[&|&]]''' 的来历相似。<ref>{{cite book|last=Cajori|first=Florian|title=A History of Mathematical Notations, Vol. 1|year=1928|publisher=The Open Court Company, Publishers|chapter=Origin and meanings of the signs + and -}}</ref>减号 '''−''' 则可能源自 m̄ 上的[[波浪号|波浪号]]，也可能只是 m 的简写。<ref>{{cite book|title=Intermediate Algebra|edition=4th|year=2000|first1=D. Franklin|last1=Wright|first2=Bill D.|last2=New|publisher=Thomson Learning|page=1|quote=The minus sign or bar, — , is thought to be derived from the habit of early scribes of using a bar to represent the letter m}}</ref>

